Class AustrianIDFrontSideRecognizerSettings

  • java.lang.Object

    android.os.Parcelable

    public class AustrianIDFrontSideRecognizerSettings
extends RecognizerSettings
    Represents a settings for setting up recognizer which can scan front side of austrian national ID cards.

    • Field Detail

      • FACE_IMAGE_NAME

        public static final java.lang.String FACE_IMAGE_NAME
        Name of the image sent to MetadataListener that contains face. This image will be sent to MetadataListener during recognition process if displaying of face image is enabled (see setDisplayFaceImage(boolean), and receiving of ImageType.DEWARPED image is enabled with MetadataSettings.ImageMetadataSettings.setDewarpedImageEnabled(boolean)
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

    • Method Detail

      • setDisplayFaceImage

        public void setDisplayFaceImage(boolean displayFaceImage)
        Sets whether face image from ID card should be sent to MetadataListener. If enabled, image will be of type ImageType.DEWARPED, and the name of the image (see Image.getImageName()) will be equal to FACE_IMAGE_NAME, so make sure you subscribe to receiving of ImageType.DEWARPED images with MetadataSettings.ImageMetadataSettings.setDewarpedImageEnabled(boolean)
        Parameters:
        displayFaceImage - whether face image should be sent to MetadataListener.
